text.tspan: Tuesday, January 2, 2029
Scabor Corporation Silent on
Teleporter Deaths
Space giant Scabor Corporation held a live launch party for its Orbital
Teleportation System (OTS) - and it ended in tragedy.
For the system's inaugural teleport, the company planned to send its
Educational Outreach Director, along with 5 students who are part of the
company's Educational Outreach program, to its low Earth orbit Station
Beta.
Scabor Corporation is the world's leader in space technologies and
Many have called into question the company's silence on the event, as
it has been 3 days since the tragedy occurred and there is still no official
statement. Scabor Corporation could not be reached for comment on this
article.
January 3, 2029 - For Immediate Release
From the desk of the Director
Dear All,
It is with deepest regret that I must inform you of the
passing of Scabor's outstanding Educational Outreach
Director and longtime friend of mine, Maxwell Edison,
along with four of our Educational Outreach Students:
Rosemary
Simon
Adam
[Y/N here]
The tragedy that occurred last Sunday resulted in the loss
of these five bright young minds, and for that I offer my
sincerest condolences and sympathies. Rest assurred that
Scabor Corporation will be conducting full investigation
into what went wrong in the Orbital Teleportation System
that resulted in this terrible event.
My deepest condolences and sympathies,
Dr. S. N. Greenfield
Director, Scabor Corporation Exploratory Science Team

g.aria-label: This document is for review by the United States Department of Defense (US DOD) and associated authorized personnel only. Unauthorized use is prohibited. Overview: The Orbital Teleportation System (OTS) is Scabor Corporation's latest innovation in medium-range transportation, allowing near-instantaneous transportation between two locations, provided each location has an OTS receiver and sender. Applications: Though the OTS was originally designed for use by Scabor Corporation and associated agencies for medium-range ground-to-orbit transportation, the system can have a wide range of applications outside of this field, especially in defense. The system can be adapted to work with only ground-based receivers and senders, allowing the client to near-instantaneously transport an individual or individuals. Range: 0 - 250 miles A joint project between Scabor Corporation's Exploratory and Defense teams, the OTS has been extensively tested to the highest standard of safety.
